Reasoning: The paper discusses the architecture of the NSDL, which is a digital library for science education. The use of metadata, annotations, and semantic relationships to provide context for the resources in the library suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DL (Digital Libraries) sub-category. The use of Fedora, a tool for representing complex content and data, suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. The focus on pedagogical value suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category, as machine learning techniques are often used in educational contexts. The use of an information network overlay suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.CY (Computational Geometry) sub-category, as this sub-category often deals with network structures. Finally, the use of metadata and annotations suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category, as this sub-category deals with natural language processing and information extraction.
